sentences: Ivan recorded and toured with the band for seven years.
In 2003, de Prume formed a new band, Healer, along with Scott von Heldt (Kurai/Theater of Madness).
In 2006, Ivan was asked to play drums on the soundtrack for Sony's Ghost Rider by Christopher Young.
In 2007, Ivan and his family relocated to the Pacific Northwest.
Burningsound Studios officially re-opened for business in January 2009.
In March 2009 Ivan began hosting a weekly metal radio show on Saturday nights called Metalopolis in Portland, Oregon for 101.1 KUFO.
